    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nI started programming in Ada and noticed an odd behaviour where there is a delay after pressing space at the end of every Ada keyword like `with`, `use`, `function`, `begin`, etc.\r\n\r\nAfter disabling my keymap in my lua configs, the issue goes away. The only thing in my keymap is a bind of leader to space.\r\n\r\nAda is the only language this happens in.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nMy keymaps.lua:\r\n\r\n```lua\r\nvim.g.mapleader = ' '\r\nvim.keymap.set('n', \"<leader>pv\", vim.cmd.Ex)\r\n```\r\n\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nI expect that Ada should behave like the other languages I use where this is not an issue. C, Haskell, OCaml, Swift, etc.\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.10.0\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nunsure\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nmacOS 14.5 and Arch Linux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nAlacritty 0.13.2\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256colour\n\n### Installation\n\nBrew and Pacman",
